result.formatted_address: 9 Yik Yam St, Happy Valley, Hong Kong
result.name: Cheung Hing Coffee Shop

reviews.text:
I was at the coffee shop for breakfast.  A 3 star means it is certainly worth a try . This may be more useful fro tourist.

Do get a combo for breakst because it is more economical than just getting a drink.

The bakery goods are nicely done.

Because it can get quite busy, you may be asked to share a table. It is common in Hong Kong.
Great traditional Hong Kong style tea restaurant. Be sure to get there early as the signature dishes sold out pretty early.
Local cafe. Good for nostalgic memberance. Suggest "tea run" and "chicken pie". Don't know what there are? Go and find out.

Best egg tarts in HK and the Yeet Lai chat.
Better call them to know when the egg tarts are coming out and do reserve otherwise can lead to disappointment

Cheung Hing coffee shop is one of the best local tea shop or cafe shop I had been to. The food is very authentic and especially my favorite there is egg tart. Others are like very great meal to have for each meal. Love it so much. Go there every time when I’m around causeway bay. Highly recommended for anyone go solo, with friends or family. The price is decent. Have a nice meal.
